<br>
&quot;You are correct, the infidels must pay. But in due time. I want to do this correctly, so something such as this may never occur again.&quot;<br>
<br>
::With that, Hades stood up. Sceptor in his hand, silver crown with an amethyst set in the center still upon his head::<br>
<br>
&quot;I need you to attempt to track down Hecate, and meet me at the mouth of the cave of the Titans with her. I will meet you there shortly, I have to retrieve someone as well.&quot;<br>
<br>
::With that, Hades walked out of his Throne room, and out of his Palace. He held his staff aloft and summoned his Chariot, drawn by two black horses, both of which breathed fire::<br>
<br>
::He then mounted his Chariot and left the gates of Tartarus::<br>
<br>
::Just in front of Hephaestus' blacksmithy in Mount Aetna, the earth shook and split open creating a large rift. There were times when Hades could slip descretely in and out of Tartarus onto Earth, and there were times when he wanted his presence pronounced. This was one of those times he wished his presence pronounced::<br>
<br>
::The chariot emerged from rift and stopped just in front of the main entrance of the smithy. Hades walked right into the shop, seeking out Hephaestus::<br>
<br>
::He merely glanced at the cyclopes hard at work. They did not utter anything in response, merely pointing in the direction of the back of the smithy. Hades approaced a large steel door and opened, almost with sheer will alone, he opened the door. No mortal could move the door, even some of the lesser gods would have a problem moving the door physically::<br>
<br>
::Hades looked directly at Hephaestus:: &quot;Your presence and help are required immediatly in Tartarus.&quot;<br>
<br>
