<br>
::The appearance of Hecate suprised him somewhat, as Hecate was a goddess that he rarely saw. He smiled cordially to her, but did not say anything as she didn't walk up, or even acknowledge his presense::<br>
<br>
::Hephaestus hammered away on the chain, his hands were now had a red glow, the same kind of glow that was in heated metal. The chain itself started taking on the same red glow that was within his hands, one could easily surmise that this was a transfer of magic::<br>
<br>
::Within what seemed no time, Hephaestus was linking the chain back together link by link, as he imbued each link with magic, as well as the lock. The glow still strong upon the chain. His hands were touching the hot chain, and not getting burned. He was of course also God of Fire.::<br>
<br>
::He then hoisted the enormous chain over his shoulder and dragged it back to the door. He placed the chain and the lock back upon the door. It still glowed a bright red. He then raised his hand. He then muttered something, and the magic stabilized upon the chain::<br>
<br>
::He then clapped his hands together:: &quot;Not the prettiest piece of work I've done, but just as strong, if not moreso. If Prometheus could not break his chains, the combined might of the Titans will NEVER break this one. Plus the magic wards I have placed upon them. Nothing will EVER get in, and nothing will EVER get out.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He then waved his hands over the pit of fire, and it began cooling. He then picked up his tools, his hammer and his anvil, though they still be hot, with no problem::<br>
<br>
&quot;Now if you'll be so kind Uncle Hades. My payment and then a return trip to Aetna.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=persephoneqofu>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 200<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/5/03 5:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.aishwarya-rai.com/tradi/tash16.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Better</span><hr size=1> ::The royal physician walks up to Hades and Hephaestus and bows kneels politely. Upon seeing the new chains, his gives a sigh of great relief::<br>
<br>
Lord Hades, her majesty the queen has woken up. She is healing much faster than we anticipated and she wishes to see you. Word has gotten round that Hephaestus is here and she is very eager to see him as well. Even though she looks much better, I will not let her awake stay for much longer. Should I inform her that you and Hephaestus shall decline? <p>*~* Persephone...Queen of the Underworld.. Faithful wife to Hades... Princess Goddess of the Spring*~*</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ixlordhadesxi>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 243<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/5/03 11:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Payment</span><hr size=1> ::Hades watched on as Hephaestus was hard at work on the chains. During the time period when the chains were removed, Hades stood perfectly still with his hands out in front of him, palms foward. His eyes were glowing dark purple. He was using all of his powers as Master of the Realm to keep that door closed, he was able to do it, though he had to maintain at least partial concentration upon it, just to be safe, he put all of it on.::<br>
<br>
::When Hephaestus was just about to finish adding magic to it, Hades walked over and touched them, placing his own magic within the chains, now should even one of the wards ever be broken, Hades would now know immediatly, and not be caugh off guard::<br>
<br>
::He maintained his concentration as Hephaestus placed the chains back upon the doors. They were now sealed up once again, hopefully for the last time::<br>
<br>
::Hades took a deep breath and then looked at Hephaestus. He walked over and placed his hand upon his shoulder and did something he RARELY ever does to ANYONE::<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank you, My Nephew. You shall be paid in full and then some. They will be delievered to your shop in Aetna by some Shades. Uncut unpolished of course. I figure you as the master-craftsman would like to do that.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He then patted him on the shoulder as the physician arrived:: &quot;We shall go see my wife. Then I shall take you back to Aetna personally.&quot;<br>
<br>
::Hades climbed onto his chariot and bid that Hephaestus does the same. When both gods are one, Hades steers it to his Palace to see Persephone. When they arrive Hades walks upstairs to see Persephone.::<br>
<br>
::He walks over to her bedside, holds her hand and then lightly kisses her cheek:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ixhephaestusxi>IX Hephaestus XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/5/03 4:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Visit</span><hr size=1> ::Hephaestus was caught off guard a little bit when Hades thanked him. He simply remained in silence, nodding in acknowledgement, but he was truly at a loss for words::<br>
<br>
::He climbed on the chariot with Hades and kept looking about during the ride. Tartarus was a rather strange place for him. It was such an oddity for him to be down here, for he had only been down here perhaps a couple of times before this::<br>
<br>
::He followed behind Hades into the palace and into Persephone's room. He stood back a few feet from the bed, allowing Hades and Persephone time to embrace. It was very strange for him to see Hades show emotion at all, though he knew that Hades did love Persephone. He simply shook his head, strange day indeed:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=persephoneqofu>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/5/03 9:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.aishwarya-rai.com/tradi/tash16.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> nice hello</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/hotsab/aish168.jpg " style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
